snippet.textDisplay:
This is the magic Indian musicians can produce. real fusion with great precision.

Coke Studio pakistan invented this wonderful platform where musical geniuses collaborate in the language of music. But they were becoming stagnant with Sufi/hindustani/qawwali compositions which even though good are now sounding very redundant.

I think its time Indian musicians take CS forward as we have much much more diverse music to take it to the next level like Carnatic music, those from the North east and much much more. if only our legendary classical singers can get a little more flexible and open to such collaborative music, I think music all heads will turn to "real" Indian music instead of boring bollywood club-music.
